      "classLessonTitle": "Dept week — light homework & review",
      "grade": "G7",
      "subject": "Art",
      "topic": "Van Gogh's Style",
      "teacherNotes": "Today the children learned what Van Gogh's style is. They looked at The Starry Night and Sunflowers",
      "gradeSubjectLine": "G7 · Art",
      "parentSummary": "What does it mean?\nIt means that today, the kids learned how a famous painter named Vincent van Gogh made his art. They didn't just look at his pictures; they learned the \"tricks\" he used to make his art look special.\n\nWhat is Van Gogh's \"style\"?\nTo explain it simply to a child or in plain talk, his style has three main parts:\n\n- Thick Paint and Lines: He didn't make his paintings smooth. He used thick paint. You can see the marks from his brush. It looks like many little \"dashes\" or \"sticks\" of color.\n\n- Bright Colors: He loved using very bright colors, like bold yellows and deep blues, even if the real object didn't look exactly like that.\n\n- Swirls and Movement: Everything in his paintings looks like it is moving. The stars look like they are spinning (swirls), and the grass looks like it is blowing in the wind.\n\nIn short:\nThe children learned to paint with bright colors and swirly, thick lines to make their pictures look full of energy and feeling.",
      "tonightActions": [
